#. +> trunk5
#: content/about.md:61
msgid "History"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/about.md:63
msgid "Kdenlive is a community project which aims to deliver a free and open source video editing software application to allow everybody to produce high quality content in order to increase the democratization of the media. The application has a graphical user interface written in C++ with [Qt][8] and uses KDE libraries for the [MLT framework][6] written by Dan Dennedy, which relies on [FFmpeg][7] to decode and encode almost all the video and audio formats that are available today, and which hosts effects libraries like Frei0r and Movit for video, and LADSPA and SOX for audio."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/about.md:67
msgid "Team"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/about.md:69
msgid "Kdenlive is developed by a small, mostly volunteer team from all over the world. New contributors are always welcome!"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/about.md:71
msgid "Here is the currently active core team:"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/about.md:75
msgid "License"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/about.md:77
msgid "This program is Free Software as described by the [Free Software Foundation][1] under the terms of the [GNU General Public License][2]."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/about.md:79
msgid "There are no license fees to pay, no registrations or subscriptions, and no premium features that require payment to be unlocked."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/about.md:81
msgid "Kdenlive is part of the KDE Community. The legal entity behind the community is [KDE e.V.][3], a German non-profit organization."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/about.md:83
msgid "Technologies"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/about.md:87
msgid "Through the MLT framework, Kdenlive integrates many plugin effects for video and sound processing or creation. Furthermore, Kdenlive brings a powerful title editor, a subtitling solution, and can then be used as a complete studio for video creation."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/about.md:89
msgid "Video effects are provided by [Frei0r][4] while audio effects use [LADSPA][5]."
msgstr ""

