#. +> trunk5
#: content/about.md:0
msgid "Project launched by Jason Wood with version 0.2.3"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/about.md:0
msgid "According to the official documents that we can find on the internet, the project was launched by Jason Wood, who released version [0.2.3 in October 2003](/news/releases/0.2.3/). Soon, Kdenlive 0.2.4 followed, but the community did not yet exist and the group was very small."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/about.md:0
msgid "Jean-Baptiste Mardelle joins the project"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/about.md:0
msgid "The project stopped for two years. Before the end of 2005, Jean-Baptiste Mardelle, who heard that the project would be re-activated, offered his help. And in 2006, he signed the [post of the new release 0.3](/news/releases/0.3/) of the program. From this moment on, he became the main reference point for the project."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/about.md:0
msgid "Major refactoring from KDE 3 to KDE 4 completed"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/about.md:0
msgid "Version 0.4 and 0.5 are soon distributed, but there is an issue. A refactoring of the code is needed to go forward. The program has to be moved from KDE 3, which is not compatible with MLT, to KDE 4. The rewriting ends in 2008, followed by several new releases."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/about.md:0
msgid "Migration from KDE 4 to KDE 5 begins"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/about.md:0
msgid "Three years later a further migration from KDE 4 to KDE 5 was needed to allow the program to grow."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/about.md:0
msgid "Crowdfunding campaign launched for project development"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/about.md:0
msgid "In 2012, a crowdfunding campaign is launched to fund the operation, and before the end of 2014, the goal is reached."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/about.md:0
msgid "Kdenlive becomes an official KDE application"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/about.md:0
msgid "Then finally, in 2015, Kdenlive becomes an official KDE application. Jean-Baptiste was invited to Akademy, KDE's annual world summit, to present ten years of activity."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/about.md:0
msgid "Windows version announced, new logo and website launched"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/about.md:0
msgid "The new perspective is to make the project even bigger. Before the end of the year, the [first Kdenlive Café](/news/historic/drupal/kdenlive-cafe-01-and-02/) is announced with the aim of getting more people involved. During this virtual meeting, it immediately became clear that in order to grow, Kdenlive needed to be cross-platform. The Windows version was [announced in 2016](/news/historic/drupal/moving-towards-a-working-windows-build/), began with a sprint meeting followed by the new logo and the new site."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/about.md:0
msgid "Timeline refactoring roadmap written"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/about.md:0
msgid "But as soon as the development of new features started, it was evident that the code for the timeline had to be rewritten, because it was too old and no longer fit for purpose. Everybody knew that the refactoring could take several months or years, but the community did not lose enthusiasm."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/about.md:0
msgid "Refactored code distributed with new features"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/about.md:0
msgid "In 2018, a roadmap was written, and in 2019, the refactored code was distributed, although some fine tuning was still needed."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/about.md:0
msgid "Continuous improvements and new features added"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/about.md:0
msgid "Then finally, since 2020, continuing up to now, the long-awaited new features along with a wide variety of new effects and dozens of important improvements have been continuously added to create the most powerful, free, and open source video editing application ever."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/bug-reports.md:12
msgid "Bugs happen. That is a fact. But they can be fixed. And the better a bug report is the easier it is for the development team to replicate, investigate, and eventually fix it."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/bug-reports.md:14
msgid "All bug reports need to be logged in the [official bug tracker][1]. And feature requests are tracked there as well using the **severity** item *wishlist*. But before you do, please do the following:"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/bug-reports.md:16
msgid "Step 1: Upgrade to the latest release"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/bug-reports.md:18
msgid "Please upgrade to the [latest released versions][2] of Kdenlive. We do not answer bug reports for old Kdenlive versions (unless they are still reproducible in latest version)."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/bug-reports.md:20
msgid "Step 2: Search the official Kdenlive documentation"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/bug-reports.md:22
msgid "RTFM - Read The Fine Manual is a phrase often used to mock users asking questions that could be answered by reading the documentation. In the days and age of YouTube tutorial this may not be as important or relevant anymore, but you are encouraged to consult the [official Kdenlive documentation][10]. It can be searched and contains a wealth of good and valuable information."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/bug-reports.md:24
msgid "Step 3: Search the forums"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/bug-reports.md:26
msgid "Kdenlive has a large community that is active in forums and chat rooms. You should check a few place to see check the whether other users encountered the same issue. Perhaps a fix or workaround exists:"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/bug-reports.md:27
msgid "The [official forum][3]"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/bug-reports.md:28
msgid "[r/kdenlive][4] subreddit"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/bug-reports.md:29
msgid "[Discord][5]"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/bug-reports.md:30
msgid "Telegram"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/bug-reports.md:31
msgid "Mastodon"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/bug-reports.md:33
msgid "Step 4: Query open issues"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/bug-reports.md:35
msgid "[Search the bug tracker][7]. Perhaps the issue you are experiencing has already been reported or is even worked on. The bug's status is a good indicator for what is currently happening:"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/bug-reports.md:38
msgid "_REPORTED_ is a bug that has been reported but nothing has happened so far. There may be a discussion about it, so it is worth checking if it may apply to your issue."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/bug-reports.md:39
msgid "_NEEDSINFO_ is a reported bug, which needs more feedback. This means, a dev team member looked at it but needs more details"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/bug-reports.md:40
msgid "_CONFIRMED_ means that the bug can be reproduced (either by other users or the dev team)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/bug-reports.md:41
msgid "_ASSIGNED_ means that a developer is handling the bug"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/bug-reports.md:42
msgid "_RESOLVED_ means that the bug was fixed in the development version"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/bug-reports.md:44
msgid "Step 5: Report the bug"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/bug-reports.md:46
msgid "If you have a crash at Kdenlive startup or when trying to play a video file, please follow this steps:"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/bug-reports.md:48
msgid "If you compiled Kdenlive and/or MLT yourself, make sure you followed all steps described in [our instructions][8]."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/bug-reports.md:49
msgid "Check that you don’t have several versions of MLT installed"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/bug-reports.md:50
msgid "Try playing your video file with FFmpeg’s player. From a terminal: `ffplay myvideo.mpg`"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/bug-reports.md:51
msgid "Try playing your video file with MLT’s player. From a terminal: `melt myvideo.mpg`"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/bug-reports.md:53
msgid "Include the results in your bug report as attachments."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/bug-reports.md:55
msgid "For a good bug report please include the following information:"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/bug-reports.md:57
msgid "Your Kdenlive and MLT version. You can copy that information from Kdenlive Menu > Help > About."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/bug-reports.md:58
msgid "Your operating system (OS), like Windows, Linux distro, or MacOS including the respective version"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/bug-reports.md:59
msgid "The installation method for Kdenlive, like Windows installer or standalone, or Linux flatpak/snap/ppa or appimage"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/bug-reports.md:60
msgid "Detailed steps to reproduce the bug. Screenshots and screen recordings are very useful for replicating the issue."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/bug-reports.md:61
msgid "Any error messages or log files you can provide. Please do **not** copy & paste log content into the bug report but add it as an attachment."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/bug-reports.md:62
msgid "If the bug crashes Kdenlive, provide a backtrace."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/bug-reports.md:64
msgid "How to get useful crash information (backtrace)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/bug-reports.md:66
msgid "A backtrace contains valuable information for the dev team. It needs a bit of OS specific setup and command line wizardy and may therefore be not everyone's cup of tea."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/bug-reports.md:68
msgid "Linux appimage"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/bug-reports.md:70
msgid "Please install the following packages: `gdb`, `kdenlive-dbg`, `libmlt-dbg` (package names may be slightly different depending on your distro)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/bug-reports.md:72
msgid "When Kdenlive crashes, if the KDE crash handler dialog pops up, you can copy the data it provides. Otherwise, start Kdenlive from a terminal like this:"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/bug-reports.md:74
msgid "Type `gdb kdenlive`"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/bug-reports.md:75 content/bug-reports.md:85
msgid "After gdb read debug symbols, type `run`"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/bug-reports.md:77
msgid "Linux Flatpak"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/bug-reports.md:79
msgid "First of all make sure the Flatpak debug symbols are installed by typing `flatpak install org.kde.kdenlive.Debug` to a command line."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/bug-reports.md:81
msgid "Now you can start the Flatpak from a command line like this:"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/bug-reports.md:83
msgid "Start a shell inside the Kdenlive Flatpak sandbox: `flatpak run --command=sh --devel org.kde.kdenlive`"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/bug-reports.md:84
msgid "Type `gdb /app/bin/kdenlive`"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/bug-reports.md:87
msgid "For more details on Flatpak debugging see here: https://docs.flatpak.org/en/latest/debugging.html"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/bug-reports.md:90
msgid "Windows"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/bug-reports.md:92
msgid "Build Kdenlive with KDE Craft locally as described [here][9]."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/bug-reports.md:93
msgid "Type to the command line `cd C:/CraftRoot/mingw64/bin`"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/bug-reports.md:94
msgid "Start gdb with `gdb`"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/bug-reports.md:95
msgid "Start Kdenlive -> get the PID number"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/bug-reports.md:96
msgid "`attach 3288` (replace 3288 by the PID number)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/bug-reports.md:97
msgid "Wait on the (gdb) prompt"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/bug-reports.md:98
msgid "Type `c`"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/bug-reports.md:101
msgid "Once you followed the platform specific instructions above to start Kdenlive, you can trigger the bug. When Kdenlive crashes, go to your terminal window and type:"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/bug-reports.md:103
msgid "`thread apply all bt full`"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/bug-reports.md:105
msgid "Then press enter until you see the full data. Copy the log to a file and attach it to the bug report."
msgstr ""

