#: content/fund/index.md:0
msgid "Fund and Support Kdenlive"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/fund/index.md:0
msgid "❤️ Donate"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/fund/index.md:0
msgid "Nested Timelines"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/fund/index.md:0
msgid "Screenshot of multiple sequence tabs in Kdenlive"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/fund/index.md:0
msgid "2023-2024"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/fund/index.md:0
msgid ""
"A much requested feature, enabling the use of multiple sequences in a project, each sequence having its own timeline.\n"
"\n"
"Sequences can then be inserted into other sequences, allowing for very flexible and powerful workflows. More about this in our [documentation][1].\n"
"\n"
"[1]: https://docs.kdenlive.org/en/cutting_and_assembling/sequence.html\n"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/fund/index.md:0
msgid "Improved Audio Waveforms"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/fund/index.md:0
msgid "The old low resolution waveform next to the improved high resolution waveform"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/fund/index.md:0
msgid ""
"The audio waveforms in Kdenlive received several much appreciated improvements thanks to the [work of Etienne André][1], who increased the performance and resolution of the audio waveforms displayed in Kdenlive.\n"
"\n"
"[1]: https://etiand.re/posts/2025/01/audio-waveforms-in-kdenlive-technical-upgrades-for-speed-precision-and-better-ux/\n"
